sentences: Eve Jihan Cooper (née Jeffers; born November 10, 1978), known mononymously as Eve, is an American rapper, singer, actress, and television presenter.
Eve Jihan Cooper (née Jeffers; born November 10, 1978), known mononymously as Eve, is an American rapper, singer, actress, and television presenter.
In 1999, she released her debut album, Let There Be Eve...Ruff Ryders' First Lady, which reached number-one on the Billboard 200, making her the third female rapper to accomplish this feat.
Eve followed up with three subsequent albums, Scorpion (2001), Eve-Olution (2002), and Lip Lock (2013).

From 2017 to 2020, Eve was one of the co-hosts of the CBS Daytime talk show The Talk.
In 2021, she starred in the American television series, Queens.
She was also featured on the album Planet Her by Doja Cat, which earned her a Grammy Award for Album of the Year nomination as a featured artist.
Eve has received multiple accolades throughout her career, which include a Grammy Award, BET Award, MTV Video Music Award, Teen Choice Award, and two Daytime Emmy Award nominations.
